hopobject.body: I'm sorry, I didn't catch your name medcloudseg.com The chancellor is expected to reveal whether or not he intends to press ahead with a split in the next few weeks. It will be the first high- profile challenge for Ross McEwan, who recently replaced Stephen Hester as the chief executive of the taxpayer-backed bank. Banking experts believe there is little chance of Osborne allowing RBS to continue in its current form and that he will propose reform of some kind.
